      • calculateSetPoint

        public double calculateSetPoint()
        Calculates the correct encoder position (in rotations) by dividing the angle in degrees by 360 and adding the current position. If the position exceeds 90 degrees in either direction, the setpoint will be set slightly before to avoid overtaxing the motor. For ensured accuracy, the encoder is recalibrated at that position.
